        <scopecontent id="ref8">
            <head>Scope and Content Note</head>
            <p>The Irwin Silver Photograph Collection spans the period from 1977-2002 and contains photographs of New York City, primarily of memorial activities after the September 11, 2001 collapse of the World Trade Center towers. The photograph titles were assigned by the photographer.</p>
        </scopecontent>
        <arrangement id="ref9">
            <head>Arrangement</head>
            <p>The collection is divided into two series: New York City September 11 Memorials; and General Photographs.</p>
        </arrangement>
        <relatedmaterial id="ref35">
            <head>Related Material at the Department of Prints, Photographs, and Architectural Collections</head>
            <p>Other photographs of the World Trade Center and the aftermath of its destruction can be found in PR 169, the World Trade Center Photograph Collection.</p>
        </relatedmaterial>
