            <c id="ref30" level="series">
                <did>
                    <unittitle>Series II: General Photographs</unittitle>
                </did>
                <scopecontent id="ref34">
                    <head>Scope and Contents note</head>
                    <p>Series II contains three photographs of New York City, which date from 1977 to 2002. Two black and white images from 1977 and 1990 show New York street scenes from the Lower East Side. A color chromogenic type C print, taken in 2002, shows a replica of the Statue of Liberty being transported from the roof of the Liberty Storage Warehouse on West 64th Street to the Brooklyn Museum of Art.</p>
                </scopecontent>
